My team is trying to use Pathplanner to program our autos. When we try to basic paths such as moving backward and turning, the robot does not track properly (Videos attached). However, the robot kind of does the movement right in real life, not perfectly, but pseudo-accurate. For example, when the robot is turning, the robot turns in real life, however, on Pathplanner it is not tracking anywhere near right. What could be wrong with our odometry?
We have mk4i swerve pods with a pigeon 2.0 for the gyro.
